reviews.review:
I know I'm late to the party because the game was released in 2013, but honestly- it aged like wine :)
I'm a big fan of Bioshock franchise, and the third addition to it is a real masterpiece:
- it looks absolutely stunning. Yeah, I know, graphics from 2013, but god, it's still so pretty - I spent a lot of time just enjoying the views and my surroundings;
- so much attention to detail and soul put into level and visual art design! All buildings look quite different (and a lot of them you can actually enter and explore!) and the locations are visually distinct, you'd never call any of them "generic"; 
- combat is incredibly engaging and satisfying. You have a huge variety of vigors (plasmids), weapons and possibilities to deal with your enemies [spoiler](like using the realm tears)[/spoiler], and it doesn't get boring or repetitive;
- AI deserves a special accolade. Enemies are pretty fun and don't do stupid things. Elizabeth is probably one of the best followers implemented in a game: yeah, maybe she doesn't do anything "exceptional", but she's really helpful in combat and exploration (not overwhelmingly though), makes interesting remarks and, the most importantly, doesn't become annoying or inconvenient - she won't block you in the doorways, she won't get stuck somewhere or run ahead and spook the group of enemies;
- main story is quite complicated, but non-trivial; characters - deep and memorable, cut scenes - just of the right length so that you won't feel you're watching a movie instead of playing a game;
- the game is incredibly polished - I played for almost 40 hours and didn't encounter a single crash or bug;
- it felt quite different from the Bioshock 1-2, but there were a lot of subtle details that reminded me of the first 2 games (not to mention the entire 2 episodes of 'Burial at Sea' DLC dedicated to those of us reminiscent for old times!)
I can probably go on and on, because this game is perhaps one of the best games I played in the last decade, and it makes me a little sad that the studio behind it (Irrational Games) 'rebranded' and hasn't released anything new since 2014, but I really, really, REALLY recommend it.
Do not be afraid of the "outdated" graphics, because it's not - just play it, believe me, you won't regret it.
